ns:common.topic.description: TSP is a programming language for the estimation and simulation of econometric models. TSP stands for \"Time Series Processor\", although it is also commonly used with cross section and panel data. The company behind the program is TSP International which was founded in 1978 by Bronwyn H. Hall.
